Feeding Obesity-Suffering Children: No Breakfast and Sausage for Dinner
More than a third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 are overweight; while 9% of schoolchildren are overweight, 5% are obese.
According to the latest study, children who are obese usually come from families that lead an unhealthy lifestyle.
We again see the importance of the environment and the patterns of behavior that accompany a person for his or her healthy development.
For example, sausage appears on the tables of children suffering from obesity, almost twice as often as in families with children with normal weight.
More than 19% of obese children ate fries for dinner on the eve of a survey related to an educational event called Obesity is not a coincidence.
Moreover, families of children suffering from obesity do not engage in sports. This, however, applies to the majority of families of modern schoolchildren - only 15% of children said that their parents find time for sports at least once a week.
The study was conducted among 900 children.
The study was conducted at the end of last academic year and involved nearly 900 primary school students across Bohemia.
The event Obesity is not an accident was held for the second year in a row, with the support of the insurance company V<0xC5><0xA1>eobecn<0xC3><0xA1> zdravotn<0xC3><0xAD> poji<0xC5><0xA1>t<0xC5><0xAF>ovna and the company Unilever.
To date, more than 12,000 pupils of 4-8 grades have joined the project.
Proper nutrition and sufficient exercise are the main determinants of a rapidly growing number of children who are either overweight or obese.
“For example, only half of the respondents said they eat five times a day, according to the breakfast-breakfast-lunch-breakfast-dinner scheme, and this is one of the unavoidable conditions of proper nutrition,” says one of the study’s findings.
No lunch and sausage in the evenings
Experts warn that even relative details such as the constant time of a family breakfast are important for healthy development.
In the Czech Republic, only 23% of schoolchildren have breakfast together.
In most families, breakfast is served separately.
The worst discovery was that in every tenth family, people do not eat breakfast at all.
And yet breakfast is the basis of the right daily diet.
The study found that fried food is more commonly consumed in families with children suffering from obesity.
Almost everyone - regardless of weight - drinks sweet refreshments every day (70%).
Although more than 40 percent of children regularly play sports, this figure is more than doubled – up to 15 percent – when it comes to their parents.
Make your own menu.
In another part of the study, the selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) were asked to make their own menu based on the proposed products and based on their tastes and preferences.
"Preferences in food in Czech children aged 12-15 years are far from ideal in terms of healthy eating."
Their favorite food includes a large number of flour, meat and sweet dishes.
“Special concern is the high popularity of sweet soft drinks,” the study concludes.
As the main meal, the pasta defeated a bird with a small preponderance.
However, the children showed almost no interest in beans, fish and vegetable dishes.
Striving for a healthy lifestyle
The study also found that children were willing to change their eating habits provided they were provided with relevant information.
“Many participants in the study control group demonstrated a significant shift in preferences toward healthy food when they filled out a questionnaire after the end of the lecture Obesity is not a coincidence,” the project’s findings said.
This was especially noticeable, for example, in the case of sweet soft drinks - more children began to prefer them just water.
In addition, as the main dish, children more often noted the bird and fish, limiting the amount of sweet dishes and pastries.
A stylist should also be a good psychologist, say professionals
In the first article about training for stylists, I looked at the amount of information in introductory classes.
I had no idea what would happen next.
Lectures by three experts in this field; tips on choosing clothes for non-standard figures; and a seminar on how it all works in real life.
Further - more.
The closer we are to the final exam, the more information and practical tasks await us.
The training takes place every Saturday and Sunday, but it is really full of information.
This time with Alenka, the director, (there are no men in the course) we discussed how to dress a woman whose body is not perfectly symmetrical.
Most women are not completely symmetrical.
One has a short neck, the other has a boy figure without proper shapes, another weighs more than normal.
The stylist should know how to visually reduce broad shoulders, lengthen the neck, or add missing volumes.
We were given tips on how to emphasize the figure of women like Jennifer Lopez, that is, the owners of more lush breasts and thighs and a narrow waist, and not to wear them too provocative.
For example, if the difference in waist and hip volume is so large that you can not pick up a skirt or pants, it is worth having at least one thing sewn to order.
You will clearly not regret the invested funds, since perfectly seated clothes are priceless.
In a skirt sewn to order, you will feel much better than in one that constantly goes down, rolls up, strips the waist, etc.
Owners of boys figures, on the other hand, can wear clothes with ruches, appliques, embroidery or folds.
Given the abundance of such information and types of figures, I’m glad I have a whole week to realize it all.
And yet, I'm afraid, it's too much, given the homework we've been given.
Each participant of the courses had to come up with two outfits for some celebrity: for the day and for the evening.
We must take into account their modern appearance, their style in clothing and the type of figure.
I'm going to wear Miranda Kerr, which you may know from Victoria's Secret's advertising campaigns.
I’m happy about myself because it’s much easier to wear than, say, Britney Spears, Christine Aguilera, who has recently improved by a ton (please keep in mind that I’m exaggerating), or the very young Selena Gomez.
We must cut clothes from magazines or find them on the Internet, print and process them with graphic programs.
Mudboard - so called the result of the work - then reflects our own style and attitude to the graphic image.
It is important to keep in mind the graphical component of the style.
The stylist not only dresses real people, but creates product pages in magazines (based on special instructions, for example, fashion bags, coats, etc.).
This is what stylist and designer Mario Kamenik told us.
But it was only on Sunday.
The stylist needs general knowledge.
The Saturday lecture, full of information about the types of figures, was revived by three guests - specialists in this field.
Stylist, Honza Pokorny; fashion designer, Jakub Polanka; and fashion photographer Ben Rench.
Jacob reminded us that fashion is an illusion and the stylist should use this fact.
A good stylist can use one item of clothing in different ways.
In this case, diversity is the key to success.
For example, a trench coat can be worn in the usual way, on top of jeans and T-shirts, like a coat; but it can also be worn on a naked body, without fasteners, like a dress.
Another option is to roll up the sleeves or lift the collar, and the whole image completely changes.
“Play with him,” he said.
Anyway, I most appreciated the following advice: "For your work you should know the rules perfectly."
Then you can start breaking them," Jacob told us.
Here I finally understood why we’re going to tame all the definitions and rules, what to combine with what and why, while in fashion magazines we often see something completely different.
Not to mention the fashion shows.
From Ben, the photographer, I learned that the stylist should have more outfit options than the number of photos he needs to take.
So, for a ten-page fashion review (equivalent to ten outfits) I should be willing to create at least fifteen images.
Now I also know that the item of clothing in the picture often looks and works in combination with others is not quite the same as in reality.
We have to keep this in mind when creating an image.
Honza Pokorny confirmed that often image and style are half the success.
Just look at Madonna, who doesn’t have an amazing vocals, but her image and marketing have turned her into a world star.
The attitude to the services of stylists in the Czech Republic is still quite cool.
Even famous people often consider it superfluous (and believe that it is enough to be an expert in something, and how they look is secondary).
And if someone finally allows us to create their style, we should expect them to call us a different (less) size than the one they actually wear.
Then we turn to Google and find out if the tabloids have written anything about some celebrity being overweight/weaned, etc.
On Sunday, Honza and Mario emphasized that it is not enough for a stylist to understand fashion and be able to pick up outfits.
Our work mainly consists of communicating with the people we dress; therefore it is important to be a good psychologist.
To be able to evaluate people, not to pretend to them and to stick to your opinion.
“If the manager asks you to look at her clothes and add a few beautiful things, you can’t throw away her entire wardrobe by telling her that her clothes are terrible.”
“Find at least a few things you can praise and advise what you can wear with them,” says Mario.
He also showed us what specifically should fit the work bag.
This is a bag that you tie around your waist to carry everything you need.
In addition to obvious things, such as scissors, a sticky roller or English pins, it should have a nylon thread (stylists use it when shooting some items, such as a bag or a hat), special clips for fastening the fabric on the back.
In order to distract ourselves from the lectures and gain some practical experience, we learned to do the right linings on the soles of shoes.
Even when shooting in a studio where the floor is smooth, the soles can get damaged - not to mention outdoor shooting.
So we did the sticker.
You should not touch the shoes with scissors so as not to spoil them.
It requires real skill.
I was glad that Mario praised my work.
These skills did not appeal to me.
This is only part of what we heard during the second part of the weekend courses.
I’m starting to realize that being a professional stylist isn’t that easy, no matter what they say.
V Need for Speed: Escape takes place in America.
Responsive
What was supposed to be a carefree walk turned into a routine morning commute to work because of a series of completely inappropriate and careless mistakes.
Ambitions have been satisfied to some extent, but it doesn’t matter, as no one clearly wanted to do the overwork.
Before the release of the new version with the subtitle "Escape" was associated with great hopes.
It was expected to move the previous Need For Speed series in a new direction; the demo versions showed that the game would take a dignified place in the racing game genre.
We were curious to see parts of the game where the main character gets out of the car and runs.
As is often the case with NFS, in the end a lot is different from what we expected.
The game is a pretty good arcade race, but the overall impression is spoiled by a few unnecessary mistakes that have been present in this series of games for several years.
So, in reality, this is not a mistake, but a manifestation of the inexplicable laziness of the developers.
The adventure begins very well.
You become part of the story, whose protagonist, Jack, decides to solve some personal problems by participating in an illegal race through America.
You get in a car on the west coast, in San Francisco, and your task is to get to New York first.
This idea has some interesting features.
The route consists of ten stages, divided into more than fifty races.
This means that each race takes place on its own route, individual stages take place in a diverse and interesting environment.
It doesn’t feel like the same thing happens in the game all the time.
Despite the fact that the schedule is at the same level as in the previous parts of the series, some tracks are nice to watch.
And yet the game does not evoke strong emotions.
Although driving a car through the desert, in the autumn suburbs or high in the snowy mountains is very pleasant.
In addition, the race from time to time brings to life an unusual detail.
For example, in the desert you get into a sandstorm, significantly reducing visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains you need to be careful not to get under the avalanche.
The individual races are pretty well organized.
There are only a few varieties, but that is enough.
For a while you try to outrun several opponents (essentially a regular race); then you try to improve the time (the standard race with a timer); or you compete with one opponent.
In addition, from time to time you run into the police, which further complicates your task.
The components on the outside of the car are new.
It’s just an interactive animation where most of the time Jack runs away from someone and you have to help him by pressing the right buttons at the right time.
It's not complicated.
Although surprisingly, these fragments are much smaller than you might expect (just three to be exact).
In fact, it turns out that it’s good for the game because this property isn’t annoying; given all of the above, it’s one of the things that makes the game more enjoyable.
The racing model follows in the footsteps of previous models.
This means that it is no longer something special, but it can not be considered a disadvantage.
If you’re looking for real life imitation, you’ll have to look elsewhere.
And yet this driving model is very suitable for dynamic racing, although better options can be found in the market.
So far, it's very good.
However, after a while, problems begin.
Unlike the driving model, the collision model is not so good.
You don’t expect complex transformations and collisions from such a game, but if you have no idea before you collide with an object, how your machine will behave, something is wrong.
Usually, by overtaking or passing cars in a dense stream, you sometimes slightly touch another machine. And yet sometimes in a practically similar situation, your machine starts to spin wildly.
Or it's crashed.
This is not so important thanks to the restart system, but it is enough to spoil the fun.
Reboots are arranged so that if you crash or go far off the track, the game brings you back to the point where it was interrupted.
However, only five restarts are available for each race.
If you use them all, you will have to start the race from the very beginning.
This is useful if something doesn’t work out, but you can’t completely rely on it.
Sometimes reboots are not enough, and you have to learn by heart a separate section of the race.
An important drawback of the game is the fact that the same things often happen in the same places.
For example, some turns need to be done in a certain way, otherwise you just won’t fit in.
In other cases, you encounter civilian cars in a specific location in the same configuration regardless of whether you arrive first, fifth, five seconds earlier or a minute later.
This is especially annoying in situations when you see your rival easily pass between two cars moving in the opposite direction, while when you are there, the cars are already located so that you either need to drive around them or slow down.
It doesn’t matter when you’re next to them; everything is arranged so that the situation always happens right in front of your nose.
Competitors have other advantages.
During the game you discover several places where, regardless of the time, the same opponent overtakes you in the same place.
This is especially evident at the end of the game, on a long bridge where you go in the opposite direction.
Obviously, your opponent has to stand in front of you no matter what.
The fact is that when it drives in front of you, it worsens your visibility, which leads to one or more accidents in this area.
You can understand the attempt to make the game more interesting and adrenaline-filled, but it is so obvious that it quickly begins to cause irritation.
Too bad, because despite the simple model of driving, the game is fun and sometimes so full of events that you do not have time to pay attention to what is happening around you.
It doesn’t matter what doesn’t make you miss – a concept with fifty unique tracks, a sequence of races or anything else.
The idea of changing cars during races is unusual.
You need to keep track of the refueling along the way, because it is on them that your car can change, despite the fact that in most cases the one you already have is quite enough.
The machines are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for cities; powerful American cars - for straight sections of the highway; and exotic super-sportsmen for technical driving, for example, on curved mountain tracks.
The main story mode is closely related to the challenge mode; this is a race on individual sections that you will learn during the game.
Here you earn for your personal business both medals and points, common for challenges and story modes.
Many options are available for a higher level of driving: from cars to profile data.
In addition, the profile is linked to the online Autolog feature, which, among other things, compares the results you have achieved with the results of other players, and provides communication with the public.
Here’s another flaw that’s hard to understand; it’s an example from the last race in sequence.
You and your car get into the subway tunnel (let’s assume that that’s it) where you run the tracks in the dark (let’s assume that’s it).
Your speedometer shows the figures from 150 to 200 km/h (let’s assume that this is the case) when suddenly a subway train flies behind you, turning your car into a pile of scrap metal.
For several days, our editors have been discussing whether no one really thought for a second during the creation of the game, or whether its creators really consider us such fools.
The technical component of the game is nothing special; but the overall impression of the video sequence is mostly pleasant, sometimes even astounding.
Although it is a pity that in some critical moments the quality of the recording, sometimes quite strongly, is declining.
This is especially true for incidents with a large number of participants, where a good recording wouldn’t help you either.
The sound is fine; the soundtrack is for the amateur.
To please as wide a youth audience as possible, the soundtrack "entered compositions from different styles"; but it is unlikely that many people will buy the game because of its music.
The overall impression of Need for Speed: Escape is rather messy.
If the game had avoided obviously unnecessary mistakes, we could honestly say that Escape is the best part of NFS in the last few years.
Either way, the game leaves a feeling of infinity.
Sure, it’s good fun, but be prepared for the flaws that will blind you as an airport spotlight.
