How do you remember your other project, Manother Love Bone?
I think we write really good songs and at the beginning it was great.
We were a band for almost three years and didn’t release a single album until the death of Andy (Andy Woods).
There was a lot of disappointment because it lasted so long, and the most important thing is that we are still close friends with Bruce (Fervazer) and Greg (Gilmore), who started with us in the group, and when I hear a song or see a photo of me, I think of the incredible person who was behind Andy, and I think of the amazing person who is behind me.
