The left and right agree on a lot of things.
Jacques Chirac, who in 1976 declared that “900,000 unemployed people will not be a problem in a country with 2 million foreign workers”, and Michel Rocar on the left, who explained in 1990 that France “cannot accept the poor from all over the world”.
The difference is only in the level of generosity
In 2005, the fear of invasion of the country by the Polish hordes of plumbers was felt by both the left and right.
