"Card-blanche" for an absolute European monarch or jump with tied legs into the abyss of nationalism - what a choice for a citizen!
No, we are not dreaming of a guillotine blade, but of a common, clear and continuous implementation of choice and democracy, this time at a pan-European level.
There are no crises in Greece, Italy, Spain, Portugal, and it is not known how many more will have to be listed, because there is only one crisis - the crisis of Europe.
Europe as a whole is subject to the dictates of markets and rating agencies, suffering from its weakness and lack of solidarity.
The whole of Europe is humiliated on the international stage.
Many are concerned about the transfer of sovereignty to Europe, but all of Europe is gradually losing its sovereignty, and with it each of its nations.
It is urgent to restore the management of the European project to the sovereignty of the people.
Because only by working together, Europeans will be able to reduce everyone’s debt burden, free themselves from the markets and prepare for the future by investing in it.
